                    </label>
                    <label class="option" onclick="checkAnswer(6, 5, 'c')">
                        <input type="radio" name="q6_5" value="c">
                        The outdoor activities may to require good weather.
                    </label>
                    <label class="option" onclick="checkAnswer(6, 5, 'd')">
                        <input type="radio" name="q6_5" value="d">
                        The outdoor activities may requiring good weather.
                    </label>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Question 6 -->
            <div class="question">
                <div class="question-number">Question 6</div>
                <p>How would you express future benefit?</p>
                <div class="options">
                    <label class="option" onclick="checkAnswer(6, 6, 'a')">
                        <input type="radio" name="q6_6" value="a">
                        This experience will improves team collaboration.
                    </label>
                    <label class="option" onclick="checkAnswer(6, 6, 'b')">
                        <input type="radio" name="q6_6" value="b">
                        This experience will improving team collaboration.
                    </label>
                    <label class="option" onclick="checkAnswer(6, 6, 'c')">
                        <input type="radio" name="q6_6" value="c">
                        This experience will improve team collaboration.
                    </label>
                    <label class="option" onclick="checkAnswer(6, 6, 'd')">
                        <input type="radio" name="q6_6" value="d">
                        This experience will to improve team collaboration.
                    </label>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="score-display" id="score6"></div>

            <div class="btn-container">
                <button class="btn btn-secondary" onclick="goToPage(5)">‚Üê Previous Exercise</button>
                <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="goToPage(7)">View Summary ‚Üí</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Summary Page -->
    <div class="page" id="page7">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="header">
                <h1>üéâ Summary & Review</h1>
                <p style="font-size: 1.1em; color: #666; margin-top: 10px;">Well done on completing all exercises!</p>
            </div>

            <div class="summary-grid">
                <div class="summary-card">
                    <h3>üìù Exercise 1: "be" verbs</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> Use "is" with singular nouns</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> Use "are" with plural nouns</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> Use clear subjects (not "It")</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> The location/price/quality is...</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> The facilities/activities are...</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="summary-card">
                    <h3>‚úèÔ∏è Exercise 2: "have/has"</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> Use "has" with singular subjects</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> Use "have" with plural subjects</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> The company/package has...</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> The providers/they have...</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> Shows possession or features</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="summary-card">
                    <h3>üéØ Exercise 3: Action verbs</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> Use "provides/offers" with singular</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> Use "provide/offer" with plural</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> The provider offers/provides...</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> Use clear company names</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> Avoid starting with "It"</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="summary-card">
                    <h3>üìç Exercise 4: "there is/are"</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> "There is" + singular noun</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> "There are" + plural noun</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> Used to introduce new information</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> Check the noun after "is/are"</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> "a variety" is singular</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="summary-card">
                    <h3>üîÑ Exercise 5: Adjective transformation</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> "convenient location" ‚Üí "The location is convenient"</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> Match subject-verb agreement</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> Singular noun + is</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> Plural noun + are</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> "staff" is usually plural</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="summary-card">
                    <h3>üí° Exercise 6: Modal verbs</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> Modal + base verb (no -s, -ing, to)</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> can = ability/possibility</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> may = possibility/permission</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> will = future action/intention</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">‚úì</span> We can enjoy... (NOT enjoys)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%); color: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 15px; margin: 30px 0;">
                <h2 style="color: white; margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: center;">‚ú® Key Grammar Rules ‚ú®</h2>
                <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 20px;">
                    <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px;">
                        <h3 style="color: white; margin-bottom: 15px;">Subject-Verb Agreement</h3>
                        <p>Singular subjects ‚Üí is, has, provides</p>
                        <p>Plural subjects ‚Üí are, have, provide</p>
                    </div>
                    <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px;">
                        <h3 style="color: white; margin-bottom: 15px;">Clear Subjects</h3>
                        <p>‚úì The company offers...</p>
                        <p>‚úó It offers...</p>
                    </div>
                    <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px;">
                        <h3 style="color: white; margin-bottom: 15px;">Modal Verbs</h3>
                        <p>Modal + base form</p>
                        <p>‚úì can enjoy  ‚úó can enjoys</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="instruction-box">
                <strong>üí° Tips for Writing Your Assessment:</strong>
                <ul style="margin-top: 15px; margin-left: 20px; line-height: 1.8;">
                    <li>Start with a clear subject (not "It")</li>
                    <li>Use correct subject-verb agreement</li>
                    <li>Mix different sentence patterns</li>
                    <li>Use modal verbs to express benefits</li>
                    <li>Transform adjectives to make varied sentences</li>
                    <li>Proofread for grammar accuracy!</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

